ady 68 and I used kind of joking. If you say that was my how do you miss myself? Hi my name is Nina. My mom died. I was nine and my dad we married a few months later later to a creep and sent me away when I was like a seventh grade limited orphanage with a bad kids and I’ve always felt like it a reject like it there was a tattoo tattoo of my forehead, and that God was just help me up by worrying me. I do not expect a normal life instead of having a normal life and having all this crap happier when I was older. So my thing is, I never knew how to feel normal like to go on a date you know we’re not worried and you know I do that if I go to bed again I would have a broken heart so I don’t spirit single you know anyway it’s really such a I like how to be because I’m pretty smart and I really have a lot of passion, important things that will be deeply, but I just can’t seem to get out of my own way and I’m self as appetizer queen but with all the shit going on, I started a program that supposed to reprogrammed my mind and then my vision started to go and I may or may not lose my mission permanently but either way I will get it. I’m just kidding. I’m gonna try and structure my thought where it says even if I only have 10 years left. You know I don’t want it to feel like this anymore so I know this is the longest comment you’ve ever received. I really not sure who you are or of your therapist or an author or or or how do I maybe take a seminar or if you have any other resources that you might direct me to that be great thank you so much for sharing and I totally agree that dude don’t you think like like you did something like you messed up somehow hell you know it so it’s your fault but I know for sure that’s what’s weird is I know that I don’t do anything wrong but it’s too hard tonight, but I think you’re still feel really damaged and sad even though you don’t wasn’t your fault and it’s really interesting. OK that’s all bye", "timestamp": 1773030446}, {"author": "jodyduk